# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ZHA frontend — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev. In Vercel, add these under
# Project Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase — REQUIRED (the only variables read at runtime).
# From Supabase → Project Settings → API.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# Service-role key — ADMIN/LOCAL ONLY. Used by one-off migration/admin scripts,
# never by the app at runtime. DO NOT add this to Vercel.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ── Audio streaming (home resolver) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# YouTube blocks streaming from datacenter IPs (Vercel), so audio is resolved AND
# streamed by a copy of this app on a home/residential IP; Vercel forwards every
# /api/innertube/pipe request there and relays the audio. Works from any network.
# See DEPLOYMENT.md for the named-tunnel + one-command setup.
#
# RESOLVER_URL — set ONLY on the hosted (Vercel) deployment: the home resolver's
# stable public URL (ngrok static domain). Leave UNSET on the home resolver
# itself (otherwise it forwards to itself in a loop).
# RESOLVER_URL=https://your-name.ngrok-free.app
#
# RESOLVER_TOKEN — shared secret; set the SAME value on Vercel and the home
# resolver so the public URL only serves authorised requests.
# RESOLVER_TOKEN=some-long-random-string
#
# YOUTUBE_COOKIE — optional. A logged-in youtube.com `cookie:` header used to
# authenticate the resolution session. Server-only secret. ToS-risky.
# YOUTUBE_COOKIE=VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE=...; __Secure-3PSID=...; ...
